footer.title: How to Choose the Right Fruit Seedling - Tips from Our Nursery
texts: When choosing fruit seedlings, it is important to pay attention to quality, variety, and rootstock, as these factors determine yield, resistance, and the longevity of the orchard. In our nursery, we offer certified seedlings of apples, pears, plums, sweet cherries, sour cherries, apricots, peaches, nectarines, quinces, hazelnuts, walnuts, grapevines, and other fruit species, grown through controlled production and carefully selected rootstocks.

All seedlings come with a certificate of origin, phytosanitary approval, and varietal purity, ensuring stable yields and uniform growth. Our experts are here to help you choose the variety that best suits your soil, climate, and market.
In addition to selling seedlings, we also provide expert advice, planting and care recommendations, as well as the option to deliver seedlings across Serbia and abroad.

aboutUs.title: Who We Are and What Makes Us Different
aboutUs.text: We specialize in producing premium-quality fruit seedlings, grown with care and expertise, for orchards that will bear fruit for generations. Our advantage lies in the combination of decades of experience, a wide assortment, and dedication to quality at every step.

benegit1.title: Quality Above All
benegit1.text: We offer only tested and healthy seedlings, grown to the highest standards. We carefully select varieties and monitor every step of production to ensure healthy and vigorous plants.

benegit2.title: Wide Assortment
benegit2.text: Our offer includes various types and varieties of seedlings, tailored to both professional orchardists and smaller producers.

benegit3.title: Expert Support
benegit3.text: Our team is here to provide advice and recommendations for the best selection and care of seedlings.

benegit4.title: Traditional Commitment and Innovation
benegit4.text: The combination of many years of experience and modern methods enables us to produce seedlings that deliver long-term results.

aboutUs.sveOnamaText:
We are engaged in the production of top-quality fruit seedlings, adapted to different climatic conditions and customer needs. Our wide assortment includes more than 15 types of seedlings - from fruit trees such as apples, pears, and cherries, to grapevines and roses - to ensure that every client finds the right plant for their space and preferred growing method.

We combine traditional expertise with modern cultivation methods, guaranteeing the quality and longevity of our seedlings. All are produced according to the highest standards and regularly undergo health and quality inspections. In addition, our seedlings are recognized on the international market, with exports to over 20 countries, confirming the reliability and high standard of our production.

We are committed to your success as well, so our team provides expert advice on planting, care, and cultivation, while fast and secure delivery ensures that the seedlings arrive in perfect condition. With us, you choose quality, expertise, and long-term reliability for your orchard.
